results.wikipedia_summary: The tapaculos (pronounced ta-pa-COO-lo) are a group of small suboscine passeriform birds with numerous species, found mainly in South America and with the highest diversity in the Andean regions. Three species (ChocÃ³, Pale-throated, and the Silvery-fronted) are found in southern Central America.
